    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>June 4-10; Shorter Lives for Americans</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By BARBARA CROSSETTE</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>By most demographic estimates, an American born in the last year or two should live, on average, to nearly 77. But the World Health Organization, using a new calculation, has lowered the figure for ''healthy life expectency'' to 70 because of the risks faced by Americans, particularly men -- smoking and violence are high on the list.</p>
        <p>BARBARA CROSSETTE</p>
      </block>
